scopecontent.p:
The 16,000 items in the papers of Walter Barton Leach (1900-1971)
span the years 1920 to 1971, with the bulk of the papers falling
within the 1940 to 1970 period. The collection includes
correspondence; memoranda; minutes of meetings; reports; transcripts;
press releases; government and other forms and form letters; official
documents; legislative bills; financial statements; drafts and
outlines of speeches and writings; typed manuscripts; proof sheets;
lecture notes; lists; tables; news clippings; printed items;
photographs; one phonograph record.

